attributes.value: A Chicago-Penn streetcar has just crossed over the railroad throat on the north edge and is crossing 3rd Avenue on 7th Street. The curving track in the foreground was used by Anoka streetcars to access their downtown depot, shared with the Dan Patch and Luce Line trains.
